{
  "rule": "weno5_advection_2d",
  "metric": "Linf",
  "max_linf_error": 0.05,
  "max_overshoot": 0.005,
  "max_undershoot": 0.005,
  "notes": "Acceptance bounds for the 2D smooth-advection canonical case. With Nx=Ny=32, the asymmetric Gaussian (sigma_x=0.1, sigma_y=0.15) is resolved by ~3-5 cells per axis. Classical Jiang-Shu (1996) 5th-order WENO with SSP-RK3 (Gottlieb-Shu 1998) on a smooth periodic field has small numerical diffusion and dispersion at CFL=0.4. After exactly one revolution in x (u=1.0, T=1.0) and two in y (v=2.0, T=1.0), the analytic solution equals the IC, and the L_inf error is dominated by the marginal y-resolution (sigma_y/dy ~ 4.8 cells). The 0.05 ceiling provides margin above the typical ~0.02 measured error and is well below the analytic peak of 1.0; overshoot/undershoot bounds confirm WENO5 monotonicity behavior on smooth fields (no spurious extrema beyond round-off at this resolution)."
}
